ProMED

[Sadly, this disease is opening up wounds for many people who are experiencing a 2nd time of the death of their birds.

The wild birds migrate, and this highly pathogenic strain of the avian influenza is closely attached to these wild birds making their southern pilgrimage. As they travel, they are leaving a wake of destruction behind them.

Protect your birds! This nightmare has not ended yet. Strengthen biosecurity, be alert to any signs of other birds in the area, move your birds inside so there is no contact with wild birds or their feces, which also can spread the disease.

We express hope that the pet emu will recover. - Mod.TG

